The paper deals with algorithms for approximating volumes of convex sets, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of convex minimization and the ellipsoid method suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the Van der Waerden and Schrijver-Valiant conjectures, which are related to algebraic complexity theory and graph theory, respectively, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on the mixed volume of convex sets suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of discrete geometry (cs.DS).
